items.name: sei_shonagon/清少納言/清少纳言 (Fate/Grand Order)
items.description:
How to Use This Model

USE THEM SIMULTANEOUSLY. In this case, you need to download both sei_shonagon_fgo.pt and sei_shonagon_fgo.safetensors, then use sei_shonagon_fgo.pt as texture inversion embedding, and use sei_shonagon_fgo.safetensors as LoRA at the same time.

それらを同時に使用してください。この場合、sei_shonagon_fgo.ptとsei_shonagon_fgo.safetensorsの両方をダウンロード する必要があります。sei_shonagon_fgo.ptをテクスチャ反転埋め込みとして使用し、同時にsei_shonagon_fgo.safetensorsをLoRAとして使用してください。

同时使用它们。在这种情况下，您需要下载sei_shonagon_fgo.pt和sei_shonagon_fgo.safetensors这两个文件，然后将sei_shonagon_fgo.pt用作纹理反转嵌入， 同时使用sei_shonagon_fgo.safetensors作为LoRA。

(Translated with ChatGPT)

The trigger word is sei_shonagon_fgo, and the recommended tags are masterpiece, best quality, highres, solo, {sei_shonagon_fgo:1.10}, yellow_eyes, black_hair, multicolored_hair, twintails, red_hair, blue_hair, smile, sunglasses, bangs, hair_ornament, bag, blush, black_nails, breasts, bow, long_hair, one_eye_closed.

How This Model Is Trained

This model is trained with HCP-Diffusion. And the auto-training framework is maintained by DeepGHS Team.

Why Some Preview Images Not Look Like Sei Shonagon Fgo

All the prompt texts used on the preview images (which can be viewed by clicking on the images) are automatically generated using clustering algorithms based on feature information extracted from the training dataset. The seed used during image generation is also randomly generated, and the images have not undergone any selection or modification. As a result, there is a possibility of the mentioned issues occurring.

In practice, based on our internal testing, most models that experience such issues perform better in actual usage than what is seen in the preview images. The only thing you may need to do is fine-tune the tags you use.

I Felt This Model May Be Overfitting or Underfitting, What Shall I Do

Our model has been published on huggingface repository - CyberHarem/sei_shonagon_fgo, where models of all the steps are saved. Also, we published the training dataset on huggingface dataset - CyberHarem/sei_shonagon_fgo, which may be help to you.

Why Not Just Using The Better-Selected Images

Our model's entire process, from data crawling, training, to generating preview images and publishing, is 100% automated without any human intervention. It's an interesting experiment conducted by our team, and for this purpose, we have developed a complete set of software infrastructure, including data filtering, automatic training, and automated publishing. Therefore, if possible, we would appreciate more feedback or suggestions as they are highly valuable to us.

items.name: Anime Artstyle LoHa (SDXL)
items.description:
• Current version: 2.0

  • Recommended weight: 0.8-1.0 (the more LoRa's are chained together the lower this needs to be)

  • Recommended VAE: SDXL 0.9

  • Recommended model: SDXL 1.0

  • Recommended inference settings: See example images

I recommend using the official SDXL 1.0 model that has the SDXL 0.9 VAE already integrated, which you can find here.

Trigger words

  • mn artstyle

Further usage notes

Note that the model currently tends to generate young looking characters. Unfortunately my dataset was quite limited (mostly Makoto Shinkai movies) to preserve quality, so it does not have many images of actual adult looking woman, due to the nature of the current anime industry of having mostly young looking characters.

Changelog

v2.0

  • Moderately improved quality

  • Closer to Makoto Shinkai's style

  • Massively improved compatibility when used in conjunction with other LoRa's

  • Increased file size

v1.0

  • Initial release

Description

Anime artstyle LoHa for SDXL 1.0 trained (not merged) by me (AI_Characters). Credit is not mandatory but I would still appreciate credit when posting images using this LoHa on social media! Feel free to @ my Twitter and/or Instagram accounts too (@ai_characters)! I would love to know when it is used!

If you want to support what I am doing, donations to my Ko-Fi would be greatly appreciated! Those will go towards funding the renting of GPUs for further experimentation and model making.

Feel free to also try out my RVC2 AI voice models which you can find here!

Stats

Dataset:

  • 133 images (screencaps)

Training:

  • rented RTX A4090 on Vast.ai

  • Training time: ~1h 30min

  • Example training configuration (v3)

All persons in this model are 21+ and not a minor, please DO NOT post explicit nudity, suggestive, or pornographic content online using this model. Refer to CivitAi TOS for more details.

===

Request or Suggestion Rule:

  1. No request for a minor!

  2. The requested should have public data (not private)

  3. Should have more than 30 good-quality images

  4. Since all requests or suggestions are free, I will still need to like your request, otherwise its a work not a hobby for me.

  5. Be a decent human being and leave a review if your request is up It takes you only 5 mins while it takes me hours, electricity, and effort to do your requests.

  6. If you don't get what you want, do not review the bomb, there could be other creators' models or Lora that can get better results than mine, use theirs instead, and leave a good review on them too, support any other creators for their complex works!

NOTE: I will keep updating more actresses in versions update

===

Usage Guide

--

A. Lora Weight

  • 0.1 ~ 0.4 -- is to combine multiple faces or features, or if you experience overbaking

  • 0.5 ~ 0.7 -- is a balanced weight to get still accurate features but with more flexibility

  • 0.8 ~ 1.0 -- is to create an accurate representation of the features.

B. CFG Scale

  • A lower CFG Scale means AI gets more creative and less overbaking problems.

  • A higher CFG Scale means results get very accurate with training sets and are more prone to overbaking problems.

  • Dynamic CFG Threshold, using this method allows you to bump up quality and achieve photorealistic quickly, but with lycoris, I found out recently that this method actually lowers the success rate, so only use it when you are composing with a Lora / model that works fine with this method.

C. Sampling Steps, High Res Fix & Upscaling

  • I like sampling steps at 50, with high res steps at 20, or 1/2 of the sampling steps.

  • I find that 2M Karras works better and faster than SDE Karras. with ERSGAN 4x+ method + ERSGAN 4x for Upscaling. This method actually gives quite good results without being too sharp or too plasticky

  • Upscaling - GPFGAN @0.25, Codeformer @0.3 & Codeformer Weight @0.15 seems to yield superior results.

Enjoy.

items.name: 荒野景观调/landscape/Architecture
items.description:
本模型使用了一些国外的景观效果图，在树、草、建筑立面等方面有明显特色表现，没有涉及水体、花海等内容

1.本模型抽离了大量画风与部分内容，这意味着在搭配cn时可以肆无忌惮的放其他lora而不担心画面过度（同样的在不用cn裸跑图时会显得整个画面没什么特别的）

本模型会使草变成荒野风格（这就意味着画面中可能会出现很多的绿色内容），可以搭配其他lora来中和画面的色彩

本模型是用basilmix炼制的，大模型建议使用chilloutmix（建筑与景观永远的神），其他也都可以

2. 本模型抽层并融合整理过，直接开1.0即可，并不会出现过度的画风过拟合，如效果不好，可以试试开启动态cfg（一个插件）

本模型最好搭配bad-picture-chill-75v,BadDream,FastNegativeV2,等负面embedding使用

本模型可搭配其他调整画面细节的lora如崔工的光影lora、FilmVelvia3等等

3.本模型定向的特色效果并不明显，这意味着他并不能成为某个定向工作的工具，但是如果想吧一个带有景观元素的效果图变得细腻一些，可以尝试使用。

（因为手头定向内容的效果图多少沾点版权，所以只能发这种比较随意的）

4. 本模型训练集不涉及商用版权，请勿用于售卖或非法盈利行为

I've only made images with this LoRA in ComfyUI using SDXL 1.0. You might get some really cool images in the newer checkpoints from the community. Overall the LoRA seems pretty flexible and can make interesting images with simple and complex prompts.

items.name: Korra Character LoHa (SDXL)
items.description:
See also my Korra character LoHa here!

  • Recommended weight: 0.8 (0.6 when used in combination with one of my other LoHa's)

  • Recommended VAE: SDXL 0.9

  • Recommended model: SDXL 1.0

  • Test inference workflow: See example images (drag and drop images into ComfyUI)

I recommend using the official SDXL 1.0 model that has the SDXL 0.9 VAE already integrated, which you can find here.

Trigger words

  • Korra

    • with lh hairstyle (season 1-3 ponytail hairstyle)

      • wearing kr outfit (season 1-3 default outfit)

      • wearing pb outfit (season 1 probending fireferrets outfit)

      • wearing sc outfit (season 1+2 winter coat)

    • with sh hairstyle (season 4 bob hairstyle)

      • wearing ek outfit (season 4 earth kingdom outfit)

      • wearing fs outfit (season 4 default outfit)

    • riding on Naga (to prompt her riding on Naga; does not work well)

  • image in lk artstyle of Korra ... (to prompt her in her native Legend of Korra artstyle, but I recommend my actual Legend of Korra artstyle LoHa for more)

Further usage tips

Outfits and hairstyles can be mixed with each other so-so. Some combinations work better than other's. You can also prompt other people with these outfits and hairstyles, but that does not work quite so well.

The model isn't 100% perfect. It may take a few tries to get full outfit likeness with a prompt, but you should be able to get a full likeness image with at least 1 image out of a batch of 4. It may also depend on the artstyle and complexity of the prompt.

There is also the issue that certain outfits (e.g. the fs outfit) seem hardcoded towards the lk artstyle, even when negative prompting it.

I will attempt to improve upon this iteration in the future!

Korra character LoHa for SDXL 1.0 trained (not merged) by me (AI_Characters). Credit is not mandatory but I would still appreciate credit when posting images using this LoHa on social media! items.name: dog-san style / bean / ドッグさんスタイル
Megumin (Konosuba)
items.description:
This model was trained on over 100 images that were meticulously tagged by hand as verbosely as possible on a slow learning rate.

In general this lora works best at strengths around 0.45-0.75 depends on the base model used, and sizes like 1024x512 or 512x1024, depending on if you want a portrait or landscape image. works fine with 512x512 as well but can be more messy and make more mistakes. base models like furry vixens usually works best (anime models tend to be burned for anime characters and produce worse results ironically)

This model has a lot of highly specific trigger tags which allow you to highly customize your output. See the example images for prompt examples, the trigger words are

lolibomber - the general trigger, included on all images as the first tag in training and set to not shuffle. If you are looking to make alt costumes or change base traits like hair color then use only this tag and none of the others. doing that you can easily make her a white hair freckle covered girl without it fighting you too much.

megu_staff_full, megu_staff_mid, megu_staff_top, megu_staff_bottom -
tags related to the staff, broken into sections to be as hyper particular as possible. for example if you want her holding it behind her back then do not include megu_staff_full or megu_staff_mid. If you want her pointing it towards the screen then do not include full, mid or bottom, etc. This will help the model realize where it needs to be. not perfect and still sometimes has issues placing it but usually can get what you what with a few batches

megu_outfit_shirt - relates to her normal dress/skirt outfit can easily be removed or added without the rest of the outfit without issue using this tag


megu_outfit_cape - just her cape, can easily be removed or added without the rest of the outfit without issue using this tag

megu_outfit_hat - the hat, can easily be removed or added without the rest of the outfit without issue using this tag, removed from head sadly usually removes is from the image entirely, i am hoping in updates to make it possible to have it in the image but just on the ground or in her hand. might need a new tag for it

items.name: Zhangzhou Lumian/Hokkien Lor Mee (Experimental, 1.0 failed)
items.description:
Experimental Lora

1.0 failed.

2.0 Lor Mee only.

1.0 NOTICE

Trigger+other tags I used in training to generate some food in random.

It can generate Zhangzhou Lumian only in some seeds.

NOTICE:

It is highly possible to generation some other foods.

I advise that you can add "Lumian" and more than 3 other triggers/tags I mentioned here to try.

第一遍测试的时候因为堆了很多料所以没发现，第二次单独材料测试的时候出现五香变蒸蛋馃或者变美少女或者变成其他的一堆吃的的情况，目前建议是使用Lumian以及至少另外三种这里提到的触发/标签。

Zhangzhou Braised noodles/Zhangzhou Lumian(Local pronunciation: Ziangziu Loomi) 漳州鲁面/漳州卤面/Hokkien Lor Mee(福建卤面, Fujian Lumian)

A kind of noodles in Zhangzhou, Fujian Province, China.

There are some other Lumian/Lor Mee in China, like Xinghua Braised noodles/Xinghua Lumian/Heng Hua Lor Mee 兴化卤面, which is from Putian, Fujian Province.

Trigger:

Lumian→noodles, egg, soup

zhengdanguo 蒸蛋馃(zim-uan 蟳丸)→a kind of advance steamed egg, usually duck egg+a little flour+minced pork belly+shrimps+xianggu(Lentinula fungi, including shiitake)+minced Chinese water chestnut (Eleocharis dulcis). Please use "zhengdanguo slices" .

bamboo shoots(sng-a 笋仔)→ dry Braised bamboo shoots. It is a pity that the bamboo shoots I used are not old enough, and not in the local shape.

wuxiang 五香→wuxiang roll, north Zhangzhou version, not the five-spicies. It also call jijuan鸡卷. At least 3 kinds of Zhangzhou wuxiang. IT SEEMS THAT WUXIANG ARE MIXED WITH ZHENGDANGUO...... wuxiang slices→zhengdanguo slices

Other tags I used/训练时使用的其他标签:

minced garlic 蒜蓉

fried minced garlic 油炸蒜丁

pork 猪肉

fried pork 炸肉片

pig intestine 猪大肠

solid pig blood 猪血

duck gizzard 鸭肫

tofu puff 豆泡

coriander 香菜/芫荽

squid 鱿鱼/柔鱼

shrimps 虾米/海米

oyster 海蛎/蚝仔

I forgot to add fried thick bean curd 油炸豆干(=厚揚げatsuage in Japanese) and dry kam cham tsoi 干金针菜.

这个漳州卤面Lora基于漳州卤面的照片训练

但是，因为材料多样，无法收集齐全部材料。

且一些东西本身模型中不存在。

卤面Lumian 对应noodles, egg, soup

蒸蛋馃zhengdanguo(蟳丸zim-uan)可以说是闽南的高级蒸蛋，但是因为断面原因这里出现了五香和蒸蛋馃混合的现象。

五香，又叫鸡卷、响铃（苏浙），是一种豆皮卷制的油炸食品。常见石码五香（一般说的漳州五香）、同安五香（泉州五香/厦门五香），漳州另外有云霄五香等，笔者知道的闽南五香有四种。因为断面问题，wuxiang slices变成和zhengdanguo slices差不多的东西

笋干bamboo shoots 素材用的不是卤料用笋所以不一样。

NAI-full-pruned

items.description:
❤️ - Ko-fi ❤️ Where creators get support from fans through donations, memberships, shop sales, and more! The original 'Buy Me a Coffee Page.;https://ko-fi.com/steverogers080863

DISCLAIMER:

I do not support any indecent images generated of all persons in this model, I do not support selling generated images of persons in this model. please refrain from what they have been posting online.

All persons in this model are 21+ and not a minor, please DO NOT post explicit nudity, suggestive, or pornographic content online using this model. Refer to CivitAi TOS for more details.

===

Request or Suggestion Rule:

  1. No request for a minor!

  2. The requested should have public data (not private)

  3. Should have more than 30 good-quality images

  4. Since all requests or suggestions are free, I will still need to like your request, otherwise its a work not a hobby for me.

  5. Be a decent human being and leave a review if your request is up It takes you only 5 mins while it takes me hours, electricity, and effort to do your requests.

  6. If you don't get what you want, do not review the bomb, there could be other creators' models or Lora that can get better results than mine, use theirs instead, and leave a good review on them too, support any other creators for their complex works!

NOTE: I will keep updating more actresses in versions update

===

Usage Guide

--

A. Lora Weight

  • 0.1 ~ 0.4 -- is to combine multiple faces or features, or if you experience overbaking

  • 0.5 ~ 0.7 -- is a balanced weight to get still accurate features but with more flexibility

  • 0.8 ~ 1.0 -- is to create an accurate representation of the features.

B. CFG Scale

  • A lower CFG Scale means AI gets more creative and less overbaking problems.

  • A higher CFG Scale means results get very accurate with training sets and are more prone to overbaking problems.

  • Dynamic CFG Threshold, using this method allows you to bump up quality and achieve photorealistic quickly, but with lycoris, I found out recently that this method actually lowers the success rate, so only use it when you are composing with a Lora / model that works fine with this method.

C. Sampling Steps, High Res Fix & Upscaling

  • I like sampling steps at 50, with high res steps at 20, or 1/2 of the sampling steps.

  • I find that 2M Karras works better and faster than SDE Karras. with ERSGAN 4x+ method + ERSGAN 4x for Upscaling. This method actually gives quite good results without being too sharp or too plasticky

  • Upscaling - GPFGAN @0.25, Codeformer @0.3 & Codeformer Weight @0.15 seems to yield superior results.

Enjoy.

items.name: Risograph-SDXL
items.description:
Introduction: Risograph is a brand of digital duplicators manufactured by the Riso Kagaku Corporation, that are designed mainly for high-volume photocopying and printing. It was released in Japan in 1980.

So what it does is, it is a printing technique best described as a ‘digital screen printing’. The process is similar to screen printing, but with the convenience of an office copier. It’s known for its vivid colours (that other printers can’t produce) and its specific textures. These machines deliver ‘perfect imperfections’ and provide a cheap and easy method for reproducing work at large quantities, like posters, prints and zines.

So this LoRA aims to produce the risograph output.
